Link to an external resource which provides the range values - e.g. a binary image file.
This provides a choice of representation. In general we try to avoid alternative representations of the same semantics. Is it justified in this case??

List of scalar values providing the values in a single component of the range. To use this encoding for complex values multiple Coverage instances must be used, each providing one band of the range. In this usage, in order to ensure that the domains of the coverage are identical, all but one should use the GML xlink:href method on the "domain" property in order to point to the domain description provided in only one place.

List of "records" providing the values of elements of the range. A choice of specific record-types are provided, with the structure and semantics of a record described in the Reference System Definition that is the value of the rangeParameters property.
